sentence: Fastenal Company ( FAST ) will begin trading ex-dividend on July 24, 2013.
A cash dividend payment of $0.25 per share is scheduled to be paid on August 23, 2013.
Shareholders who purchased FAST stock prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment.
This represents an 25% increase over the prior quarter.
At the current stock price of $46.9, the dividend yield is 2.13%.
The previous trading day's last sale of FAST was $46.9, representing a -12.14% decrease from the 52 week high of $53.38 and a 17.25% increase over the 52 week low of $40.
FAST is a part of the Consumer Services sector, which includes companies such as Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) and Lowe's Companies, Inc. ( LOW ).
FAST's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $1.48.
Zacks Investment Research reports FAST's forecasted earnings growth in 2013 as 10.42%, compared to an industry average of 14%.
For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the FAST Dividend History page.
